# Exclude Folium-rendered map outputs from GitHub language statistics.
#
# The 12 HTML files in gallery/ are publication-ready showcase artifacts
# (~45 MB total). They render interactively on github.com and are part of
# the project's portfolio surface — they should stay in the repo.
#
# But by raw byte count they dwarf the ~170 KB of Python that actually
# defines the project, which made GitHub's language detector classify
# optitrek as primarily HTML. `linguist-generated=true` keeps the files
# in the repo (and in diffs, just collapsed by default) but excludes
# them from the language stats.
gallery/*.html linguist-generated=true

# Force LF line endings for shell scripts. The repo has `core.autocrlf=true`
# locally on BRONTOSAURUS, which converts LF→CRLF on Windows checkout. Bash
# under WSL Ubuntu can't execute a script with `#!/usr/bin/env bash\r` —
# `env: 'bash\r': Permission denied` is the symptom (exit code 126). Triggered
# during the 2026-05-24 ferry rollback when a fresh `git checkout` of the
# filter scripts re-CRLF'd them and broke the rebuild.
#
# Python doesn't care about line endings (the parser strips \r), but it's
# good hygiene and avoids surprises in test_data files or shebang-driven
# scripts.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
